[SN]TITLE[SN]
Former vicar charged with further Isle of Man sex assaults

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A retired vicar has appeared in court to face two new charges of indecently assaulting a girl under the age of 13.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Graham Gregory, 81, of Brockfield Park Drive, York, is accused of two offences between 15 July 1975 and 15 July 1977.
Mr Gregory, who also faces two similar charges, did not enter a plea when he appeared at Douglas courthouse on Thursday.
All the offences are alleged to have taken place on the Isle of Man. He was bailed until 27 April.
In February, the retired vicar appeared in court accused of two separate indecent assaults.
One relates to an alleged attack on a girl under the age of 13 in 1990, the second, against a female between 1 January 1987 and 31 December 1988.
